This ABI is for ARM-based CPUs that support at least the ARMv5TE instruction set. This is a very old version, the lack of hardware support for floating-point calculations, there are performance bottlenecks when you need a lot of computing

Supported ABIs:
● armeabi

This ABI is for MIPS64 R6. It is rarely used in mobile phones, can be ignored

Supported ABIs:
● mips64
● mips

This ABI is for MIPS-based CPUs that support at least the MIPS32r1 instruction set. It is rarely used in mobile phones, can be ignored

Supported ABIs:
● mips

This ABI is for 32-bit ARM-based CPUs which extends armeabi to include several CPU instruction set extensions

Supported ABIs:
● armeabi
● armeabi-v7a

This ABI is for ARMv8-A based CPUs, which support the 64-bit AArch64 architecture. It includes the Advanced SIMD (Neon) architecture extensions

Supported ABIs:
● armeabi-v7a
● armeabi
● arm64-v8a

This ABI is for CPUs supporting the instruction set commonly referred to as "x86-64". This intel 64-bits ABI is generally used for plates

Supported ABIs:
● x86
● x86_64

This ABI is for CPUs supporting the instruction set commonly known as "x86", "i386" or "IA-32". This intel 32-bits ABI is generally used for plates

Supported ABIs:
● x86
● armeabi (some performance loss)
